<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 9. Niphargus arolaensis sp. nov. A pleopod II B-D uropods I-III E telson." , "Figure 8. Niphargus arolaensis sp. nov. A-E pereopods III-VII." , "Figure 7. Niphargus arolaensis sp. nov., mouthparts A labrum B labium C left mandibular palp D left mandible E right mandibular palp F right mandible G, H maxilla I I, K maxilla II L maxillipeds." , "Figure 6. Niphargus arolaensis sp. nov. A antenna I B antenna II C gnathopod I D gnathopod II. The dactylus on gnathopod I (grey dashed) is added from the other body side." , "Figure 5. A new Niphargus species from Switzerland. Niphargus arolaensis sp. nov. (holotype, female 7.8 mm). The two diagnostic features (seven comb-like spiniform setae on the outer lobe of maxilla I and two spiniform setae on the lower distal part of the first urosomite near the insertion of uropod 1) are highlighted on the figure." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/547217" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/547212" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/547215" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/547216" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/547213" .

